## Scaling Notes

For large projects (20+ acceptance criteria):

### Grouping by Module

Create sub-sections within phases:
- Phase 2.1: Auth Module
- Phase 2.2: Payments Module
- Phase 2.3: Notifications Module

### Sub-Phase Notation

Use decimal notation for granular tracking:

| Phase | Task | Description | Covers | Blocked By | Status |
|-------|------|-------------|--------|------------|--------|
| 2.1.1 | Auth: Login | Implement login flow | AUTH-AC1 | 0.1 | |
| 2.1.2 | Auth: Logout | Implement logout flow | AUTH-AC2 | 2.1.1 | |
| 2.2.1 | Pay: Checkout | Payment processing | PAY-AC1 | 2.1.1 | |

### Dependency Tracking

Add "Blocked By" column when tasks have dependencies:

```markdown
- [ ] **Task 2.2.1**: Implement payment processing
  - Blocked By: Task 2.1.1 (requires authenticated user)
  - [ ] Subtask: Create payment service
  - Covers: PAY-AC1
```

### Split Files Strategy

For very large projects (50+ criteria), consider:
- `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_AUTH.md` — Auth module tasks
- `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_PAYMENTS.md` — Payment module tasks
- `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` — Index linking to module files
